                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Gresham informs Mr. Porter that the commission for the settlement of claims
                    has expiled by limitation, having disposed of twenty-five cases, leaving
                    eighteen not disposed of, and instructs him to ascertain whether Chile will
                    consent to a convention to create another commission as it is earnestly desired
                    by the United States.</p>
            </div>
